## Tagging summary

During scanning, the app computes per‑tag statistics:

```js
const tagStats = {};
for (const ev of parsedEvents) {
  const tags = ev.tags || [];
  for (const t of tags) {
    if (!tagStats[t]) {
      tagStats[t] = { events: 0, files: new Set() };
    }
    tagStats[t].events += 1;
    tagStats[t].files.add(ev.fileName);
  }
}
```

These are rendered into a single line below the raw event count, for example:

```text
Tagging summary: #cal/work – 30 events in 5 files; #cal/personal – 25 events in 6 files
```

This helps users understand how tags are distributed across events and files before they configure calendars.

